text.NRSV:
20:1 May the Lord answer you in the day of trouble, the Name of the God of Jacob defend you;
20:2 Send you help from his sanctuary and strengthen you out of Zion;
20:3 Remember all your offerings and accept your burnt sacrifice;
20:4 Grant you your heart's desire and prosper all your plans.
20:5 We will shout for joy at your victory and triumph in the Name of our God; may the Lord grant all your requests.
20:6 Now I know that the Lord gives victory to his anointed; he will answer him out of his holy heaven, with the victorious might of his right hand.
20:7 Some put their trust in chariots and some in horses, but we will call upon the Name of the Lord our God.
20:8 They are brought down and fallen, but we are risen and stand upright.
20:9 O Lord, give victory to the king and answer us when we call.

124:1 If the Lord had not been on our side, let Israel now say;
124:2 If the Lord had not been on our side, when enemies rose up against us;
124:3 Then would they have swallowed us up alive in their fierce anger toward us;
124:4 Then would the waters have overwhelmed us and the torrent gone over us;
124:5 Then would the raging waters have gone right over us.
124:6 Blessed be the Lord! he has not given us over to be a prey for their teeth.
124:7 We have escaped like a bird from the snare of the fowler; the snare is broken, and we have escaped.
124:8 Our help is in the Name of the Lord, the maker of heaven and earth.

134:1 Behold now, bless the Lord, all you servants of the Lord, you that stand by night in the house of the Lord.
134:2 Lift up your hands in the holy place and bless the Lord;
134:3 The Lord who made heaven and earth bless you out of Zion.

136:1 Give thanks to the Lord, for he is good, for his mercy endures for ever.
136:2 Give thanks to the God of gods, for his mercy endures for ever.
136:3 Give thanks to the Lord of lords, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:4 Who only does great wonders, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:5 Who by wisdom made the heavens, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:6 Who spread out the earth upon the waters, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:7 Who created great lights, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:8 The sun to rule the day, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:9 The moon and the stars to govern the night, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:10 Who struck down the firstborn of Egypt, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:11 And brought out Israel from among them, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:12 With a mighty hand and a stretched-out arm, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:13 Who divided the Red Sea in two, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:14 And made Israel to pass through the midst of it, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:15 But swept Pharaoh and his army into the Red Sea, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:16 Who led his people through the wilderness, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:17 Who struck down great kings, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:18 And slew mighty kings, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:19 Sihon, king of the Amorites, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:20 And Og, the king of Bashan, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:21 And gave away their lands for an inheritance, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:22 An inheritance for Israel his servant, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:23 Who remembered us in our low estate, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:24 And rescued us from our enemies, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:25 Who gives food to all creatures, for his mercy endures for ever;
136:26 Give thanks to the God of heaven, for his mercy endures for ever.

146:1 Hallelujah! Praise the Lord, O my soul! I will praise the Lord as long as I live; I will sing praises to my God while I have my being.
146:2 Put not your trust in rulers, nor in any child of earth, for there is no help in them.
146:3 When they breathe their last, they return to earth, and in that day their thoughts perish.
146:4 Happy are they who have the God of Jacob for their help! whose hope is in the Lord their God;
146:5 Who made heaven and earth, the sea, and all that is in them; who keeps his promise for ever;
146:6 Who gives justice to those who are oppressed, and food to those who hunger.
146:7 The Lord sets the prisoners free; the Lord opens the eyes of the blind; the Lord lifts up those who are bowed down;
146:8 The Lord loves the righteous; the Lord cares for the stranger; he sustains the orphan and widow, but frustrates the way of the wicked.
146:9 The Lord shall reign for ever, your God, O Zion, throughout all generations. Hallelujah!

148:1 Hallelujah! Praise the Lord from the heavens; praise him in the heights.
148:2 Praise him, all you angels of his; praise him, all his host.
148:3 Praise him, sun and moon; praise him, all you shining stars.
148:4 Praise him, heaven of heavens, and you waters above the heavens.
148:5 Let them praise the Name of the Lord; for he commanded, and they were created.
148:6 He made them stand fast for ever and ever; he gave them a law which shall not pass away.
148:7 Praise the Lord from the earth, you sea-monsters and all deeps;
148:8 Fire and hail, snow and fog, tempestuous wind, doing his will;
148:9 Mountains and all hills, fruit trees and all cedars;
148:10 Wild beasts and all cattle, creeping things and winged birds;
148:11 Kings of the earth and all peoples, princes and all rulers of the world;
148:12 Young men and maidens, old and young together.
148:13 Let them praise the Name of the Lord, for his Name only is exalted, his splendor is over earth and heaven.
148:14 He has raised up strength for his people and praise for all his loyal servants, the children of Israel, a people who are near him. Hallelujah!

149:1 Hallelujah! Sing to the Lord a new song; sing his praise in the congregation of the faithful.
149:2 Let Israel rejoice in his Maker; let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.
149:3 Let them praise his Name in the dance; let them sing praise to him with timbrel and harp.
149:4 For the Lord takes pleasure in his people and adorns the poor with victory.
149:5 Let the faithful rejoice in triumph; let them be joyful on their beds.
149:6 Let the praises of God be in their throat and a two-edged sword in their hand;
149:7 To wreak vengeance on the nations and punishment on the peoples;
149:8 To bind their kings in chains and their nobles with links of iron;
149:9 To inflict on them the judgment decreed; this is glory for all his faithful servants. Hallelujah!
